To estimate the COad desorption rate constants, we monitor the peak area of the linearly bound COad at the vicinity of 2060 cm−1 in SEIRA spectra at −0.2 VRHE, at which no CORR is expected to occur17,45. CO-saturated 0.1 M KOH was first delivered to the cathode compartment. After the establishment of CO adsorption equilibrium, i.e., when the CO band intensity became time-independent, the electrolyte was switched to Ar-saturated 0.1 M KOH. The desorption of COad was monitored by the decrease in the intensity of the corresponding band in SEIRAS. Representative spectra of Cu(OD) and Cu(OD)0.8Ag0.2 are shown in Fig. 2b. The areas of the CO band were integrated, normalized, and plotted with respect to time (Fig. 2c), in which the COad desorption rate constant (KD) could be estimated by fitting with the first-order desorption rate expression of the form461θCO,t=θCO,0exp(−KDt)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
